  "texts": [
    "An important class of publishers that belong under that third point are aggregation sites.",
    "Such sites either do not produce original content, or intersperse articles from (usually more reputable) other sources through their content.",
    "While the collection of articles as a whole might express some editorial bias, for the most part, these sorts of publisher introduce noise into an already noisy labelling scheme.",
    "We manually re-mapped all URL domains to a set of publishers consistent across years, excluding all news aggregation platforms and social media sites (see Tables B.2 and B.3).",
    "It should be noted that the 2018 edition of NELA did not contain URLs, making relabelling in this manner impossible."
